Teacher Appreciation Week is here again, but with school closed its missing something.

Celebrating our teachers will be a little more challenging this year, but not impossible. Here are some ways to show your support from your home:

Post a photo or video along with a message of gratitude to a teacher who inspired you.

A picture of yourself with your favorite teacher, past or present;

A picture of your child with his or her teacher;

A picture of yourself holding a piece of paper with a simple message saying Thank You to a teacher and why you‚Äôre thanking him or her.

You can use ‚ÄúIt‚Äôs Teacher Appreciation Week! Thank you [INSERT TEACHER NAME] for making a difference in my life.‚Äù
Or, write your own personal message.

Use the hashtag #ThankATeacher #QEACares when sharing.

Quality Education Academy family and community, help us thank the Black Philanthropy Initiative for awarding us with a $5000 grant.

The grant will be used to help our scholars with remote learning.

It takes a village to raise a child and our village keeps growing because QEA cares.

Again, thank you Black Philanthropy Initiative. Your grant will be used to change the world for the better.
shared_text:
Black Philanthropy Initiative
April 29 at 6:00 PM ¬∑

The Black Philanthropy Initiative (BPI) of The Winston-Salem Foundation offers annual grants that focus on Advancing Equity in Education in Forsyth County. Due to the unprecedented challenges being experienced in the community as a result of COVID-19, BPI will postpone its traditional spring grant cycle, instead making direct investments to local schools to address
equity issues around remote student learning.

Quality Education Academy was awarded a $5000 grant from the Black Philanthropy Initiative recognizing that technology and Internet access have become a heightened equity issue with the closing of schools.

Quality Education Academy is extremely proud of our scholars and educators for continuing to learn and educate with the same energy and passion we would normally see, but without missing a step. Especially during these trying and uncertain times.

Therefore, we will honor Spring Intersession as previously outlined on our school calendar.

QEA will be closed April 10th for Good Friday and Spring Intersession will begin Monday, April 13th and continue through Friday, April 17th.

We will not distribute intersession packets because everyone could use a break.

Stay healthy and be safe.

Quality Education Academy will be open tomorrow, Friday, March 27 to distribute the second round of learning packets for our scholars. Pick up hours will be from 8:00 am to 12:30 pm. Packets will be delivered at curb-side as we continue to follow social distancing protocols.

Also please bring the completed packets you received earlier this month for teachers to grade and assign credit for your scholar.

Thank you for your participation and continue to stay safe and healthy during this time.

As always, please feel free to call the school or email your scholar's teacher if you have any questions.

Continue to check our website and Facebook page for regular updates and information. Thank you!

The lottery will take place next Thursday, March 26th at 6:00 pm via web conferencing.

A link to attend the web conference will be made available soon.

As always, continue to check our website and Facebook page for regular updates and information.

post_text:
QEA teachers are preparing work packets for all students today, Monday, March 16th. Packets will be available for parent pickup tomorrow, Tuesday, March 17th, at the entrance of your scholar's school building from 8:00 am - 4:00 pm.

Additionally, teachers will reach out to parents and students regarding online work options.

QEA School Nutrition Services will provide breakfast and lunch for students during the closure.

Breakfast is available for pickup from 8:00 am - 9:00 am at the main entrance of the elementary school building. Lunch is available for pickup from 11:30 am - 12:30 pm in the same location.

All meals will be served in to-go boxes for easy pickup. Additional information regarding a mobile meal location will be made available later today.

Continue to check our website and Facebook page for additional information.

post_text:
Quality Education Academy will be closed beginning Monday, March 16th by executive order of Gov. Roy Cooper. The closure is expected to last for at least 2 weeks.

We will continue to keep the health and safety of our scholars and staff in the forefront of all decision making.

While this is an ever-changing environment that we are operating in, it is our hope to send you updates as quickly as possible.

Additional information will be sent out to parents and students in the next few days.

Please continue to check our website and social media outlets for updates.

Tonight was our 2nd Annual, Daddy-Daughter Dance. It was even bigger and better than last years dance. We had over 100 guests. Our Ladies were beautiful, as always, and our Fathers looked sharp!

The community and the families of QEA looked powerful and proud tonight. We couldn't do this without strong relationships and close bonds between our teachers, our scholars and our families.

Here are just a few photos from tonights event.

post_text:
Quality Education Academy is honored to welcome Mr. Joshua White as our next guest speaker.

Mr. White is a first-year sophomore attending North Carolina A&T State University State University. He is double majoring in Physics and Chemical Engineering.

Mr. White was selected for an internship from NASA - National Aeronautics and Space Administration and Cornell University's Astrophysics Research Program.

Tomorrow he will share with our scholars, college GPA and internship strategies that will set our Pharaohs on a path for collegiate success.

The event starts at 10:00 am in the High School Auditorium.
